Distribution
This apparent paradox is explained by the complex money-sharing procedure implemented by UEFA.
For this year, the organisation chaired by Michel Platini plans to earn 1090 million from the Champions League.
Of this amount, UEFA will spend 413.1 million on fixed payments: each of the 20 clubs that took part in the qualifying matches (including Atletico Madrid) received 2.1 million.
